@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Revenue Statistics (UC29)

autonumber
actor "Store Admin" as Owner
participant "Admin Dashboard\n(JS / Browser)" as View
participant "DashboardController\n(API Controller)" as DashController
participant "ReportController\n(API Controller)" as RepController
participant "DashboardService\n(Service)" as DashService
participant "RevenueService\n(Service)" as RepService
participant "OrderRepository" as OrderRepo
database "MySQL" as DB

== 1. View Dashboard Overview ==

Owner -> View : Access Admin Dashboard
View -> DashController : getDashboard()
note right: GET /api/admin/dashboard
DashController -> DashService : getDashboardData()

DashService -> OrderRepo : calculateTotalRevenue()
OrderRepo -> DB : SELECT ...
DB --> OrderRepo : total
DashService -> OrderRepo : countOrders()
DashService -> OrderRepo : findRecentOrders()

DashService --> DashController : DashboardResponseDTO
DashController --> View : 200 OK (DashboardResponseDTO)
View --> Owner : Display Overview (Charts, KPIs)

== 2. Generate Detailed Revenue Report ==

Owner -> View : Select time period and Click "Filter"
View -> RepController : getRevenueReport(startDate, endDate)
note right: GET /api/admin/reports/revenue
RepController -> RepService : getDetailedRevenueReport(startDate, endDate)

group Data Aggregation
    RepService -> OrderRepo : calculate Total Revenue & Group by Order Type
    OrderRepo -> DB : SELECT SUM... GROUP BY type
    DB --> OrderRepo : onlineRevenue, offlineRevenue
    
    RepService -> OrderRepo : findFiltered(...)
    OrderRepo -> DB : SELECT orders within date range
    DB --> OrderRepo : List<Order>
    
    RepService -> RepService : Group revenue by Day/Month
end

RepService --> RepController : RevenueReportDTO
RepController --> View : 200 OK (RevenueReportDTO)

View --> Owner : Render Revenue Charts & Data Table

== 3. Export Revenue Report ==

Owner -> View : Click "Export to Excel"
View -> RepController : exportRevenueReport(startDate, endDate, format="xlsx")
note right: GET /api/admin/reports/revenue/export
RepController -> RepService : exportRevenueReport(...)
RepService --> RepController : byte[] fileData
RepController --> View : 200 OK (Content-Disposition: attachment)
View --> Owner : Prompt File Download

@enduml